00:46:21.233 --> 00:46:23.275
Couldn't get it
out of my head for years.

498
00:46:23.942 --> 00:46:26.567
Nice little housewife, three little kids,

499
00:46:26.775 --> 00:46:30.275
nice husband, wasn't porkin' around,
no financial problems.

500
00:46:31.025 --> 00:46:35.108
One day outta the clear blue sky,
she does 'em. All of 'em.

501
00:46:35.317 --> 00:46:36.317
Used a knife

502
00:46:36.483 --> 00:46:37.942
she got for a wedding present.

503
00:46:38.983 --> 00:46:41.275
Didn't even deny it. Sweet as honey.

504
00:46:42.192 --> 00:46:43.983
Said she didn't know why she done it.

505
00:46:58.067 --> 00:47:00.275
- Hi.
- Am I disturbing you?

506
00:47:01.275 --> 00:47:02.275
No. Come on in

507
00:47:04.358 --> 00:47:05.317
Let's go upstairs.

508
00:47:23.525 --> 00:47:25.525
I'm using you
for my detective in my book.

509
00:47:26.525 --> 00:47:27.567
You don't mind, do you?

510
00:47:31.900 --> 00:47:35.400
I was just gonna make
myself a drink. Do you want one?

511
00:47:35.775 --> 00:47:36.650
No, thanks.

512
00:47:36.942 --> 00:47:39.942
Oh, that's right. You're off
the Jack Daniels too, aren't you?

513
00:47:44.317 --> 00:47:46.400
Got a, uh, few more questions to ask you.

514
00:47:46.567 --> 00:47:47.775
I have some for you too.

515
00:47:48.442 --> 00:47:49.358
For my book.

516
00:47:59.692 --> 00:48:01.817
You have something against ice cubes?

517
00:48:03.108 --> 00:48:04.192
I like rough edges.

518
00:48:05.233 --> 00:48:06.358
So what do you wanna ask me?

519
00:48:08.525 --> 00:48:09.775
How does it feel to kill someone?

520
00:48:13.317 --> 00:48:14.275
You tell me.

521
00:48:16.400 --> 00:48:17.650
I don't know. But you do.

522
00:48:20.608 --> 00:48:22.275
It was an accident. They...

523
00:48:22.483 --> 00:48:23.650
They got in the line of fire.

524
00:48:27.775 --> 00:48:30.942
Four shootings in five years.
All accidents?

525
00:48:33.317 --> 00:48:35.733
They were drug buys.
I was working undercover.

526
00:48:38.150 --> 00:48:40.025
You wanna tell me about
Professor Goldstein.

527
00:48:44.442 --> 00:48:46.150
Well, there's a name from the past.

528
00:48:46.317 --> 00:48:49.067
You want a name from the present?
What about Hazel Dobkins?

529
00:48:51.567 --> 00:48:54.108
Noah Goldstein was my counselor
in my freshman year.

530
00:48:55.525 --> 00:48:58.233
That's probably where I got the idea
for the icepick. For my book.

531
00:49:00.733 --> 00:49:02.733
Funny how the subconscious works.

532
00:49:03.400 --> 00:49:04.567
Hilarious.

533
00:49:06.858 --> 00:49:07.900
Hazel is my friend.

534
00:49:08.067 --> 00:49:10.567
Well, your friend
took out her whole family.

535
00:49:10.983 --> 00:49:13.775
Yes. She's helped me understand
homicidal impulse.

536
00:49:13.942 --> 00:49:15.983
Thought you would learn that at school.

537
00:49:17.650 --> 00:49:21.858
Only in theory. But you know
all about homicidal impulse...

538
00:49:22.942 --> 00:49:23.942
don't you, Shooter?

539
00:49:27.400 --> 00:49:29.108
Not in theory, in practice.

540
00:49:30.150 --> 00:49:32.858
What happened? Did you get sucked into it?

541
00:49:34.067 --> 00:49:35.483
Did you like it too much?

542
00:49:38.525 --> 00:49:40.108
I don't know what you're talking about.

543
00:49:43.150 --> 00:49:44.775
Tell me about the coke, Nick.

544
00:49:47.733 --> 00:49:49.650
The day you shot those two tourists...

545
00:49:50.858 --> 00:49:52.275
how much coke did you do?

546
00:49:56.275 --> 00:49:59.233
Come on. You can tell me.

547
00:50:05.775 --> 00:50:08.442
- I didn't.
- Yes, you did.

548
00:50:09.608 --> 00:50:11.483
They never tested you, did they?

549
00:50:13.567 --> 00:50:14.900
Internal Affairs knew.

550
00:50:18.025 --> 00:50:20.275
Your wife knew too, didn't she?

551
00:50:26.358 --> 00:50:28.108
She knew what was going on.

552
00:50:31.692 --> 00:50:33.525
Nicky got too close to the flame.

553
00:50:41.483 --> 00:50:42.692
Nicky liked it.

554
00:50:48.108 --> 00:50:49.858
That's why she killed herself.

555
00:51:06.108 --> 00:51:07.025
Hiya, hon.

556
00:51:12.192 --> 00:51:13.608
You two have met, haven't you?

557
00:51:23.108 --> 00:51:26.858
You're gonna make
a terrific character, Nick.

558
00:51:36.992 --> 00:51:38.867
She's on the phone.
She'll be right with you, detective--

559
00:51:39.825 --> 00:51:42.033
Oh. I'm gonna
have to give you a call back.

560
00:51:42.325 --> 00:51:44.700
- Detective. Detective, you can't go in--
- Let me call you back.

561
00:51:45.825 --> 00:51:46.992
Who's got access to my file?

562
00:51:47.158 --> 00:51:50.117
- What are you talking about, Nick?
- Who has access to my goddamn file?

563
00:51:50.325 --> 00:51:53.742
Nobody. It's a confidential
psychiatric record, it would be illegal.

564
00:51:53.908 --> 00:51:56.617
Don't do it. Don't you fucking lie to me.

565
00:51:57.325 --> 00:51:58.700
- It's Internal Affairs. Was it?
- No.

566
00:51:59.117 --> 00:52:00.492
- No, Nick. Please.
- Who.

567
00:52:01.283 --> 00:52:02.533
It's, uh.. Nilsen.

568
00:52:14.783 --> 00:52:15.825
What do you want, Curran?

569
00:52:15.992 --> 00:52:17.825
You sold her my file, didn't you?

570
00:52:18.700 --> 00:52:20.033
What are you talking about?

571
00:52:20.658 --> 00:52:22.033
Catherine Tramell.

572
00:52:22.408 --> 00:52:23.533
How much did she pay you?

573
00:52:23.992 --> 00:52:25.242
Hey. Come on!

574
00:52:25.408 --> 00:52:26.450
- Let him go!
- Stop it!

575
00:52:27.742 --> 00:52:28.533
How much?

576
00:52:28.742 --> 00:52:29.533
Come on.

577
00:52:30.825 --> 00:52:33.783
Hey, back off. Just back off, Curran.

578
00:52:34.617 --> 00:52:36.617
Nice and easy now. Nice and easy.

579
00:52:37.867 --> 00:52:39.658
You fucked yourself, Shooter. You hear me?

580
00:52:39.825 --> 00:52:40.617
- You are out!
- Take it easy.

581
00:52:41.033 --> 00:52:43.408
- Cool it. Take it easy.
- You are out! You're out.

582
00:52:43.617 --> 00:52:45.867
- Okay, okay.
- Save it. Save it.

583
00:52:48.533 --> 00:52:49.450
Nick!

584
00:52:50.033 --> 00:52:52.325
- What's going down, hos?
- Nothing, all right. I'll be okay.

585
00:52:52.492 --> 00:52:54.033
No, sir. You won't.
They're gonna want your badge.

586
00:52:54.200 --> 00:52:55.533
I'm tired of being played with.

587
00:52:55.742 --> 00:52:58.158
You got a real conclusive way
of demonstrating that.

588
00:53:04.450 --> 00:53:07.325
She knows where I live and breathe.

589
00:53:09.617 --> 00:53:11.283
She's coming after me, Gus.

590
00:53:12.783 --> 00:53:14.200
What is it you got between you?

591
00:53:17.700 --> 00:53:18.575
I don't know.

592
00:53:19.117 --> 00:53:20.117
It's something though.

593
00:53:21.992 --> 00:53:22.992
Something.

594
00:53:24.075 --> 00:53:24.867
Yeah.

595
00:53:34.283 --> 00:53:38.117
George Jefferson is unfair.
He's short with no hair.

596
00:53:41.575 --> 00:53:42.533
Nick?

597
00:53:44.492 --> 00:53:45.533
Nick, are you there?

598
00:53:45.950 --> 00:53:48.325
Go away, Beth. I don't wanna see you.

599
00:53:55.742 --> 00:53:56.950
I still have my key.

600
00:53:59.908 --> 00:54:01.533
Put 'em on the table and leave.

601
00:54:05.408 --> 00:54:07.033
Put 'em on the goddamn table
and leave?

602
00:54:07.242 --> 00:54:10.117
Damnit. Don't shut me out.
You owe me more than that.

603
00:54:12.742 --> 00:54:14.450
I don't owe you anything.

604
00:54:15.950 --> 00:54:17.700
You don't owe me anything.

605
00:54:18.825 --> 00:54:21.283
We went to bed, what, ten, 15 times?

606
00:54:21.492 --> 00:54:24.242
Maybe it wasn't memorable enough
to, to carry an obligation.

607
00:54:27.033 --> 00:54:30.867
- Sometimes I really hate you.
- Oh! Why don't you get yourself

608
00:54:31.033 --> 00:54:34.617
some friendly little therapist
and work out some of that hostility?

609
00:54:35.075 --> 00:54:36.658
And maybe you can get off once in a while.

610
00:54:41.575 --> 00:54:42.575
Are you nuts?

611
00:54:53.617 --> 00:54:54.950
I'm sorry...

612
00:54:56.950 --> 00:54:58.158
I don't usually act like that.

613
00:54:59.908 --> 00:55:01.450
How could you give him my file?

614
00:55:02.283 --> 00:55:03.283
I had to.

615
00:55:04.742 --> 00:55:07.033
He was going to recommend
your discharge from the force.

616
00:55:08.075 --> 00:55:10.700
He didn't buy my evaluation.
He said I wasn't objective.

617
00:55:11.158 --> 00:55:13.950
So I made a deal with him to review
the session notes himself.

618
00:55:15.200 --> 00:55:16.658
I didn't think he'd show them to anybody.

619
00:55:17.742 --> 00:55:18.700
You did it for me?

620
00:55:19.492 --> 00:55:22.200
Yes. I care about you.
I did it for you.

621
00:55:28.158 --> 00:55:31.408
Go away, Beth. Please, just go away.

622
00:56:00.033 --> 00:56:00.950
Yo.

623
00:56:06.242 --> 00:56:07.200
I'm on my way.

624
00:56:59.575 --> 00:57:03.492
One shot. Close range.
Probably a .38 caliber revolver.

625
00:57:05.283 --> 00:57:06.242
Give me your gun, Nick.

626
00:57:16.700 --> 00:57:17.658
You think that--

627
00:57:23.200 --> 00:57:26.575
I don't, hos,
but I got the minority opinion.

628
00:57:31.533 --> 00:57:32.492
Okay. I went after him.

629
00:57:34.450 --> 00:57:35.325
I lost my temper.

630
00:57:36.075 --> 00:57:38.950
You have any evidence that he showed
your psychiatric file to anyone?

631
00:57:40.783 --> 00:57:41.742
No.

632
00:57:46.033 --> 00:57:47.533
We'll speak with you afterwards,
Dr. Garner.

633
00:57:47.700 --> 00:57:49.117
I'd like to sit in. If you don't mind.

634
00:57:49.283 --> 00:57:50.658
- I'd really rather wait until after--
- I don't see anything wrong

635
00:57:50.825 --> 00:57:54.158
with Dr. Garner sitting in
if Detective Curran doesn't object.

636
00:57:59.867 --> 00:58:00.992
Where were you last night?

637
00:58:01.492 --> 00:58:02.575
Home. Watching TV.

638
00:58:03.033 --> 00:58:03.992
All night?

639
00:58:05.575 --> 00:58:06.533
Yes. All night.

640
00:58:07.700 --> 00:58:08.575
Were you drinking?

641
00:58:13.325 --> 00:58:14.325
Yeah, I was drinking.

642
00:58:14.700 --> 00:58:15.950
When did you start drinking again?

643
00:58:16.367 --> 00:58:17.367
Couple of days ago.

644
00:58:17.617 --> 00:58:21.117
I saw Detective Curran at his apartment
about ten o'clock last night.

645
00:58:21.283 --> 00:58:22.533
He was sober and lucid.

646
00:58:23.117 --> 00:58:25.700
I asked him in my capacity
as his departmental therapist

647
00:58:25.867 --> 00:58:27.908
about his altercation with Lt. Nilsen.

648
00:58:28.492 --> 00:58:30.783
He expressed regret
and displayed no hostility.

649
00:58:32.575 --> 00:58:33.825
How long were you at his apartment?

650
00:58:33.992 --> 00:58:35.158
About 15 minutes.

651
00:58:35.783 --> 00:58:38.075
I saw there was no reason
for my concern and left.

652
00:58:39.533 --> 00:58:41.367
There's no smoking in this building,
detective.

653
00:58:43.658 --> 00:58:45.367
What are you gonna do?
Charge me with smoking?

654
00:58:47.367 --> 00:58:48.325
Oh, for Christ--

655
00:58:48.533 --> 00:58:51.950
All right, Nick, I'm gonna ask you
this just once: for the record,

656
00:58:52.242 --> 00:58:53.700
did you kill Marty Nilsen?

657
00:58:56.200 --> 00:58:57.200
No.

658
00:58:58.992 --> 00:59:01.200
Come on. I'm gonna storm
into his office in front of everybody

659
00:59:01.367 --> 00:59:02.867
in the middle of the day
and kill him that night?

660
00:59:03.825 --> 00:59:04.950
I'm not that dumb.

661
00:59:05.367 --> 00:59:07.533
Going after him before
gets you off the hook for killing him.

662
00:59:07.700 --> 00:59:08.658
That's your alibi.

663
00:59:09.408 --> 00:59:12.492
Like writing a book about killing a guy
gets you off the hook for killing him.

664
00:59:12.700 --> 00:59:13.575
Good point.

665
00:59:13.950 --> 00:59:15.533
I don't understand.
What are you talking about? What book?

666
00:59:15.908 --> 00:59:17.200
Private joke, asshole.

667
00:59:17.367 --> 00:59:18.492
I don't think it's funny.

668
00:59:19.533 --> 00:59:21.117
You're going on leave, Curran...

669
00:59:21.825 --> 00:59:24.283
pending the outcome
of a psychiatric evaluation.

670
00:59:36.283 --> 00:59:38.367
Beth! I'll get my stuff in a minute.

671
00:59:41.575 --> 00:59:42.450
Beth!

672
00:59:44.492 --> 00:59:45.283
Thank you.

673
00:59:49.867 --> 00:59:51.075
It's the least I could do.

674
00:59:52.033 --> 00:59:54.742
Considering, I got you into this mess
with those reports.

675
00:59:54.908 --> 00:59:56.617
No. I mean it, thank you.

676
00:59:59.700 --> 01:00:02.075
How do you know Catherine Tramell
saw your file?

677
01:00:02.533 --> 01:00:04.867
She know things about me
that I only told you.

678
01:00:06.450 --> 01:00:07.783
She must really be something...

679
01:00:08.992 --> 01:00:10.367
from a clinical point of view.

680
01:00:11.575 --> 01:00:12.783
What was she like in school?

681
01:00:13.033 --> 01:00:15.700
I hardly knew her.
She gave me the creeps, though.

682
01:00:16.408 --> 01:00:17.367
I don't know why.

683
01:00:22.158 --> 01:00:24.742
Get some rest. Promise?

684
01:00:30.908 --> 01:00:32.242
Beth. I didn't mean what I said
yesterday--

685
01:00:32.408 --> 01:00:33.450
Yes you did.

686
01:00:34.992 --> 01:00:36.783
I'm a big girl. I can handle it.

687
01:01:01.450 --> 01:01:03.825
- Hey, you take care of yourself.
- What did you find out about the parents?

688
01:01:04.908 --> 01:01:05.950
You're on leave, man.

689
01:01:07.783 --> 01:01:10.658
You're on psycho leave. I mean,
I'm talking to a possible whacko here.

690
01:01:11.117 --> 01:01:13.492
Well, you know I'm whacko, Sam.
What did you find out?

691
01:01:17.617 --> 01:01:18.575
The boat blew.

692
01:01:19.783 --> 01:01:23.033
There was a leak in the fuel line.
There have been two previous repairs.

693
01:01:23.200 --> 01:01:24.867
They had a five mil policy on both of 'em.

694
01:01:25.075 --> 01:01:27.117
A real heavy investigation,
but they got zilch.

695
01:01:27.575 --> 01:01:30.117
Big goose-egg. It was an accident.

696
01:01:30.283 --> 01:01:31.992
IA's gonna talk to you
more about Nilsen.

697
01:01:32.158 --> 01:01:33.825
They're handling the investigation,
we're not.

698
01:01:33.992 --> 01:01:36.367
You stay in touch with Dr. Garner,
it'll help on the evaluation.

699
01:01:36.950 --> 01:01:38.033
She killed him, Phil.

700
01:01:40.242 --> 01:01:42.492
- Beth? Now you've got Beth killing people?
- No, Catherine Tramell.

701
01:01:42.658 --> 01:01:43.575
It's part of her game.

702
01:01:44.617 --> 01:01:47.242
First you've got her stealing your file.
Now you've got her killing Nilsen.

703
01:01:48.033 --> 01:01:50.658
Forget about her for Christ sake?
Go somewhere. Sit in the sun.

704
01:01:50.867 --> 01:01:53.450
- Ger her the hell out of your system.
- You don't buy it, do you?

705
01:01:54.575 --> 01:01:56.075
She knew nobody would buy it.

706
01:01:56.825 --> 01:01:59.658
She knew I'd say she did it.
And she knew that nobody would buy it.

707
01:02:00.158 --> 01:02:02.408
She is screwing with your head, Nick.

708
01:02:02.617 --> 01:02:03.408
Stay away from her.

709
01:02:31.158 --> 01:02:32.408
I heard about what happened.

710
01:02:41.358 --> 01:02:42.942
What good's a shooter without his gun?

711
01:02:44.400 --> 01:02:45.900
How exactly did you find out?

712
01:02:46.358 --> 01:02:49.858
I have attorneys. They have friends.
I have friends.

713
01:02:50.775 --> 01:02:52.692
Money buys a lot of attorneys and friends.

714
01:02:53.275 --> 01:02:55.275
Well, I wouldn't know about that.
I don't have any money.

715
01:02:55.608 --> 01:02:58.733
I don't have any attorneys,
and Gus is my only real friend.

716
01:02:59.358 --> 01:03:00.983
I wasn't talking about real friends.

717
01:03:06.067 --> 01:03:07.400
Why doesn't Gus like me?

718
01:03:09.233 --> 01:03:10.192
I like you.

719
01:03:11.817 --> 01:03:13.275
- You do?
- Yes.

720
01:03:15.358 --> 01:03:16.942
You wanna go upstairs and have a drink?

721
01:03:19.650 --> 01:03:21.108
I didn't think you'd ask me.

722
01:03:22.817 --> 01:03:24.775
Then I guess you don't know
your character that well.

723
01:03:25.358 --> 01:03:28.317
Maybe, but we're learning.

724
01:03:29.233 --> 01:03:31.275
Pretty soon I'll know you better
than you know yourself.

725
01:03:31.983 --> 01:03:33.983
- Don't be too sure.
- Why not?

726
01:03:34.733 --> 01:03:36.400
- I'm very unpredictable.
- Unpredictable?

727
01:03:46.858 --> 01:03:48.650
You ought to put some warmth
into the place.

728
01:03:49.400 --> 01:03:51.442
You don't want it to reflect
on your personality.

729
01:03:51.900 --> 01:03:53.150
I'm not trying to fool anybody.

730
01:03:54.233 --> 01:03:56.108
Jack Daniel's all right?
It's gonna have to be.

731
01:03:56.567 --> 01:03:57.650
- Ice?
- Yeah, great.

732
01:04:07.233 --> 01:04:08.025
I was expecting you.

733
01:04:13.150 --> 01:04:15.358
K-mart. A buck sixty-five.

734
01:04:21.025 --> 01:04:22.400
Why don't you let me do this for you?

735
01:04:31.108 --> 01:04:32.692
You like watching me do it, don't you?

736
01:04:36.608 --> 01:04:41.067
Could I have a cigarette too, please?
See, I told you you'd start smoking again.

737
01:04:41.567 --> 01:04:42.525
Would you light it for me?

738
01:04:49.483 --> 01:04:50.317
Thanks.

739
01:04:53.317 --> 01:04:55.233
So how much
did you pay Nilsen for my file?

740
01:04:57.900 --> 01:04:59.900
Isn't he the policeman
that you shot, Shooter?

741
01:05:02.650 --> 01:05:04.400
What if I asked you
not to call me Shooter?

742
01:05:04.775 --> 01:05:07.400
Okay. How about if I call you Nicky?

743
01:05:09.733 --> 01:05:11.192
My wife used to call me Nicky.

744
01:05:12.733 --> 01:05:15.317
Yeah, I know. I like it.

745
01:05:20.692 --> 01:05:23.233
Cheers. My friends call me Catherine.

746
01:05:24.150 --> 01:05:25.733
What Manny Vasquez used to call you?

747
01:05:26.483 --> 01:05:27.483
